Pre-Game Insights: Eswatini and Mali lock horns at the Mbombela Stadium in neutral South Africa on Tuesday at the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers.
Ranked 155th in the world, the King's Shield were beaten 1-0 by Guinea-Bissau in their previous game.
Mali fought back to earn a point against Mozambique, having fallen behind in the 37th minute but equalized after the break.
This will be the first official encounter between the sides.
The Eagles are winless in their last three games, drawing their most recent two.
The King's Shield are winless in their last seven games and have failed to score in their last four.
Mali is ranked 53rd in the world while Eswatini is 102 places lower, according to the latest FIFA World Rankings.
